<item>
            <title>[AMQ-2613] Persistent Cross-site Scripting in /createDesitnation.action [JMSDestination parameter]</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/AMQ-2613</link>
                <project id="12311210" key="AMQ">ActiveMQ Classic</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;GET /createDestination.action?JMSDestinationType=queue&amp;amp;JMSDestination=%22%3E%3Cscript%3Ealert%28%22persistent%20XSS%22%29%3C%2fscript%3E&lt;br/&gt;
This GET request creates a queue name that has malformed queue name due to lack of input validation.  After sending this request a sample of the effect can be seen by browsing to /queues.jsp and clicking on the &quot;Home&quot; link.  &lt;br/&gt;
I do not know the affected version information yet.  Is there some way I can find it?    &lt;br/&gt;
Additionally, this is vulnerable to cross-site request forgery as well but XSS is a more critical bug than XSRF (at least at this point for me I guess).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;p&gt;CVE Identifier issued for this:&lt;br/&gt;
CVE-2010-0684&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;Linux environment.&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
